{
  "doc_id": "853",
  "text": "Aortic aneurysm with the risk of acute dissection is an important cause of mortality in the western world [CITATION_1] . The prevalence of thoracic aortic aneurysms is estimated around 0.3% in the normal population [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Most patients with a dilated aorta or aortic aneurysm are asymptomatic. The diagnosis can be made as during screening in the context of a positive family history or by coincidence on imaging examinations performed for other purposes like lung cancer screening [CITATION_4] . However, acute dissection is often the first presentation, in which case over 50% of all patients die within 30 days [CITATION_5] .",
